00:27.816 --> 00:30.249
♪ All these
buckets of rain ♪

00:30.284 --> 00:32.152
♪ I've heard enough about it ♪

00:32.186 --> 00:35.157
♪ you say that I lied ♪

00:35.191 --> 00:37.192
♪ I am a gentleman ♪

00:37.226 --> 00:39.965
♪ didn't I ask for
a place I could stay ♪

00:40.000 --> 00:41.868
♪ what were we both thinking ♪

00:41.903 --> 00:44.340
♪ the next part
just got in the way ♪

00:44.374 --> 00:48.046
♪ you were just always
talking about changing ♪

00:48.081 --> 00:50.148
♪ changing ♪

00:50.182 --> 00:52.516
♪ what if I was
the same then ♪

00:52.551 --> 00:53.784
♪ same then ♪

00:53.818 --> 00:57.187
♪ the same I always was ♪

00:57.222 --> 01:05.428
♪ ♪

01:05.462 --> 01:07.131
♪ all these things
that you say ♪

01:07.166 --> 01:10.136
Hey, watch it!

01:10.170 --> 01:12.607
♪ The mind-numbing games
that you play ♪

01:12.642 --> 01:14.609
♪ I am a gentleman ♪

01:14.644 --> 01:16.079
♪ didn't I pay
for every laugh, every dime ♪

01:16.114 --> 01:17.983
[Sneezes]

01:18.018 --> 01:19.385
Excuse me,
I wasn't getting out of line.

01:19.419 --> 01:20.853
Just needed to--

01:20.888 --> 01:22.288
you're the one
who almost ran me over.

01:22.322 --> 01:25.092
I didn't see anyone
at the O.H.B. crosswalk.

01:25.127 --> 01:26.795
Well, I wasn't actually
in the crosswalk.

01:26.829 --> 01:27.796
There you go.

01:27.830 --> 01:29.498
Drip coffee. Black.

01:29.532 --> 01:31.334
♪ And then you
feed me some line ♪

01:31.368 --> 01:34.538
♪ I won't hear one more word
about changing ♪

01:34.572 --> 01:37.109
Two, lots of milk
and lots of sugar.

01:38.812 --> 01:40.413
Coffee.

01:40.447 --> 01:43.484
At your 10:00.

01:43.518 --> 01:45.152
Thanks.

01:45.187 --> 01:47.423
This Alpha Barbie
almost mowed me down

01:47.457 --> 01:49.059
in the parking lot
this morning,

01:49.093 --> 01:50.394
and then she took
my spot in line

01:50.428 --> 01:51.562
at the coffee cart.

01:51.596 --> 01:53.131
You had me
at "Alpha Barbie."

01:53.165 --> 01:55.633
So the day's already
conspiring against you?

01:55.668 --> 01:57.236
Yes.

01:57.270 --> 01:58.838
Are you dressed for
a wedding or a funeral?

01:58.872 --> 02:02.208
A little bit of both.

02:02.242 --> 02:03.676
You are standing
in front of the new head

02:03.711 --> 02:05.812
of the Office
of Congressional Affairs.

02:05.846 --> 02:07.747
That's huge!

02:07.781 --> 02:08.815
Congratulations!

02:08.848 --> 02:10.350
Thanks.

02:14.722 --> 02:16.689
Wait.

02:16.723 --> 02:21.193
Your desk isn't cleaned up.
It's cleaned off.

02:21.228 --> 02:22.995
You're leaving?

02:23.030 --> 02:24.564
Well, you went
from thrilled for me

02:24.598 --> 02:26.567
to sad for you
in two seconds.

02:26.601 --> 02:28.103
You're gonna lose
your covert status.

02:28.137 --> 02:30.305
Am I gonna be able
to see you?

02:30.339 --> 02:31.841
We'll make it work.

02:31.875 --> 02:34.911
But not like this.
Not every day.

02:34.945 --> 02:39.216
Believe it or not,
this was a very hard decision.

02:39.250 --> 02:41.185
And I'll still be keeping
an eye on you,

02:41.219 --> 02:43.788
so to speak.

02:43.822 --> 02:45.456
The O.C.A.
is a great job.

02:45.491 --> 02:46.824
It is.

02:46.859 --> 02:49.160
And you'll be on the seventh
floor with the big boys.

02:49.194 --> 02:51.396
Can always come by
and visit.

02:51.430 --> 02:54.632
Just make
an appointment first.

02:54.666 --> 02:58.202
Groan. Eye roll.

02:58.237 --> 03:01.305
Briefing time, Annie.

03:01.340 --> 03:03.874
Sounds like somebody's day
is about to get better.

03:03.909 --> 03:05.543
I heard something
about NASA.

03:05.577 --> 03:06.678
Really?

03:06.712 --> 03:08.980
You've forgotten me already.

03:14.554 --> 03:16.489
Good luck today.

03:16.524 --> 03:18.525
Thanks.

03:22.097 --> 03:24.598
Have fun with the astronauts.

03:29.538 --> 03:31.405
This area
of Northwestern Colombia

03:31.439 --> 03:34.241
is now friendly to Colombia's
rebel army, FARC.

03:34.276 --> 03:36.811
Just to orient you,

03:36.846 --> 03:39.714
Colombia's Batallon Cartagena
military base.

03:39.749 --> 03:41.083
This is what
our analysts saw

03:41.117 --> 03:44.520
over Batallon Cartagena
for two hours yesterday.

03:44.554 --> 03:45.955
The area went dark.

03:45.989 --> 03:49.291
The first images
following the blackout

03:49.326 --> 03:52.895
show at least ten LAV-150s
near the base's perimeter.

03:52.929 --> 03:54.296
FARC's spreading
its wings.

03:54.331 --> 03:55.464
They've gotten bolder,

03:55.499 --> 03:57.032
and, as the satellite
corruption proves,

03:57.067 --> 03:58.801
more sophisticated.

03:58.835 --> 04:00.769
If FARC
takes the border area,

04:00.804 --> 04:02.204
they could drive
into Panama itself

04:02.238 --> 04:04.774
and conceivably overtake
the Canal Zone.

04:04.808 --> 04:08.445
This represents a very real
danger to U.S. interests.

04:08.479 --> 04:10.914
NASA wants a discreet
domestic inquest

04:10.949 --> 04:12.983
into its satellite
maintenance program.

04:13.018 --> 04:14.819
If this can happen
to one U.S. satellite,

04:14.853 --> 04:16.620
it could happen
to all of them.

04:16.654 --> 04:19.324
Jai, I want you and Annie
to work on the inquest team,

04:19.358 --> 04:20.826
along with Reva.

04:20.860 --> 04:22.227
Who's Reva?

04:22.262 --> 04:23.495
Auggie's replacement.

04:23.530 --> 04:25.798
No one can ever
replace Auggie Anderson,

04:25.832 --> 04:29.568
but Reva Kline, everyone.

04:29.603 --> 04:31.303
Reva came from science
and technology

04:31.338 --> 04:33.572
where she was the youngest
lead project manager

04:33.606 --> 04:35.140
ever to hold that position.

04:35.175 --> 04:36.408
Let's make her feel at home.

04:36.442 --> 04:40.445
Hi.
It's good to be here.

